        walkthrough = '1. Talk to Kaede in Port Bastok at (J-5) - nearest to Home Point #1 (E) - in the north most house for a cutscene.\n   - (if she says "I heard somebody at the warehouse saying that the people from Aht Urhgan are sneaky.", disregard it and talk to her again.)\n2. Talk to Kagetora at (F-6), inside the door to Warehouse 2.\n3. Return to Kaede\'s house and speak with Ensetsu at (I-5) for a cutscene.\n   - The quest log entry will appear after this cutscene.\n4. Travel to (K-8) within Korroloka Tunnel, Map 5.\n   - The quickest entrance is from Western Altepa Desert at (M-8), via the Survival Guide. This entrance will bring you directly to Map 5.\n   - Although the Survival Guide to Zeruhn Mines is also close.\n5. Click on the ??? to spawn 3 Korroloka Leeches.\n   - These leeches will link with any Thread Leeches in the vicinity.\n   - If for some reason you click on the ??? and the Leeches don\'t pop, try relogging.\n6. Once the leeches are defeated and after the bodies despawn, click on the ??? to receive the [Key Item] Strangely shaped coral.\n   - Multiple players may do this quest at the same time for the coral:\n     - Have one member spawn it. After the Leeches are defeated and despawn, have the other players select the ??? for the coral before the spawning player.\n     - Note: If the person who spawned the leeches is KO\'d, do not raise them until after the Korroloka Leeches have been defeated. Otherwise, they will respawn immediately.\n7. Return to Ensetsu  in Port Bastok at (I-5).\n8. Travel to Norg and speak with Ryoma at (H-8), who will give you the [Key Item] Sealed dagger.\n9. Return to Ensetsu to complete the quest.',
